    "body": "You could just have several scoped locks (like with your suggestion below to include a name for the lock), and test whether they all succeed. That would however be different from the code above (which unlocks everything as soon as a failure occurs).\n\nEDIT: The problem to do it correctly with only one line of code is that you do need a conditional block of code somewhere that depends on the lock, which is simply not doable with a scoped lock (except using exceptions maybe...). \n",
